  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The functional form of the prior, which is standard and motivated by computational ease, consists of a normal, uniform, inverted gamma density combined with a degenerated inverted Wishart density for i, making the prior conditionally conjugate.",
    "The Bayes theorem is used to calculate the posterior density of the model's parameters, which is a normalised product of the likelihood and the prior (Jarociński 2010).",
    "Due to the prior's conditional conjugacy, all conditional posterior densities can be conveniently and numerically analysed using the Gibbs sampler because they are all normal, inverted gamma, or inverted Wishart (Gelman et al. 1995).",
    "The estimation procedure employs Gelman et al. (1995) 's hierarchical linear model modified by Jarociński (2010).",
    "The concept of similarity is formalised as a Gaussian prior for each country's coefficients that is centred on the countries' common mean-an exchangeable prior."
  ],
